.help gadisplay August2012 gemini.gsaoi
.ih
NAME
gadisplay -- display GSAOI images
.ih
USAGE
gadisplay inimages
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls inimages
List of raw or prepared GSAOI images to reduce.\fIinimages\fR Can be a list of
image names or numbers (comma separated or @ lists), or a range of images
numbers - wild cards are supported. The image names may include the directory
path. The images must be in multi-extension FITS (MEF) format. The file
extension ".fits" may or may not be included. See help for GAIMCHK for examples
of all syntax allowed.
.le
.ls frame = 1
Display frame for image to be loaded in
.le
.ls rawpath = ""
Path to the directory where the images are located. One may
set this parameter if the raw data are not located in the current
working directory, or specify a path in the input image file names.
If \fIrawpath\fR is supplied it will be prefixed to any path given as part of
the input image names.
.le
.ls rootname = ""
Root name of image(s) if supplying image number(s); blank for today's UT. For
example, rootname="S20120101S". If \fIrootname\fR=\fIgaprep_pref\fR a
GAPREPAREd version with the \fIgaprep_pref\fR will be display instead if it
exists in the current working directory.
.le
.ls gapfile = ""
Bad pixel file with information about the array gaps in
.le
.ls badpix = "gsaoi$data/gsaoibpm_high_full.fits"
Static MEF bad pixel mask.
.le
.ls colgap = 153
Average vertical gap between arrays (trimmed, full-frame)
.le
.ls linegap = 148
Average horizontal gap between arrays (trimmed, full-frame)
.le
.ls fl_fixpix = no
Interpolate across chip gaps?
.le
.ls fl_norm = no
Normalize each array if image is not already flat fielded?
.le
.ls fl_nodqo = no
Turn off all data quality and BPM overlays?
.le
.ls fl_bpmover = no
Overlay static Bad Pixel Mask?
.le
.ls fl_satnl = yes
Flag non-linear/saturated pixels?
.le
.ls fl_usedq = no
Use data quality planes instead of static BPM?
.le
.ls fl_imexam = no
Enter imexamine when displaying image?
.le
.ls time_gap = 0
Time in seconds to leave before displaying images, when \fIfl_imexam\fR=no
.le
.ls z1 = 0., z2 = 0.
Lower and upper limit for display if not auto scaling. See help for DISPLAY
command for more information.
.le
.ls ztrans = "linear" (linear|log|none|user)
Grey level transformation. See help for DISPLAY command for more information.
.le
.ls nonlin = 32000
Non-linearity level to use if keyword not found.
.le
.ls satura = 50000
Saturation level to use if keyword not found.
.le
.ls gaprep_pref = "g"
Prefix for GAPREPAREd images.
.le
.ls key_datasec = "DATASEC"
Header keyword for data section
.le
.ls key_ccdsec = "CCDSEC"
Header keyword for array section
.le
.ls key_nlc = "NONLINEA"
Header keyword for non-linearity level
.le
.ls key_sat = "SATURATI"
Header keyword for saturation level
.le
.ls sci_ext = "SCI"
Name of the MEF extension containing the science data.
.le
.ls var_ext = "VAR"
Name of the MEF extensions containing the calculated variance planes.
.le
.ls dq_ext = "DQ"
Name of the MEF extensions containing the data quality information.
.le
.ls logfile = ""
Name of the logfile. The default value makes use of the logfile
defined by gsaoi.logfile.
.le
.ls verbose = yes
Print actions to screen.
.le
.ls status = 0
Exit status will be non-zero if the procedure halted
with an error. This parameter is set by the task and should not be
modified by the user.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION

GADISPLAY displays GSAOI data (raw, prepared and mosaiced). If the images are
not mosaiced they are pasted into one extension then displayed. Depending on
the flags set and or the presence of data quality planes in the input images,
overlays of bad, non-linear and saturated pixels can be displayed too.

.ih
EXAMPLES

.nf
   cl> gadisplay 30-45 rootname="S20120101S" rawpath=rawdir$ time_gap=5
.fi

This will display images 30-45 with rootname of "S20120101S", e.g.,
S20120101S0030.fits, located in the directory specified by the IRAF
environmental variable "rawdir". There will be a gap of 5 seconds between
displaying each image.
.ih
SEE ALSO

DISPLAY, IMEXAM

.endhelp